molecule to depress orexinergic neurons in the hypothalamus. Absence or disruption of the gut microbiota alters sleep behavior and
metabonomics. Alterations in gut microbiota composition and butyrate levels are associated with insomnia, and colonization with imbalanced
gut microbiome from insomnia patients induces insomnia-like phenotype in recipient mice. Butyrate signaling to hypothalamus orexin
neurons can modulate sleep behavior, and butyrate supplementation ameliorates sleep disturbances in recipient mice.
